==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Formicate
<hw>For"mi*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>formica</ets> an ant.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Resembling, or
pertaining to, an ant or ants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Formicate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Formicate
<hw>For"mi*cate</hw> <pr>(f⟦ocir⟧r"m⟦icr⟧*k⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>v.
i.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Formication</er>.]</ety> <def>To creep or crawl
like ants; swarm with, or as with, ants.</def></p>

<p><q>An open space which <qex>formicated</qex> with peasantry.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Formication</ent>⟦br⟧
